      </div>
      <h1 class='title'>Powers of court where civil partners are living apart by agreement</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='grand-committee-report-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HL Deb 17 May 2004 vol 661 cc300-1GC</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_300gc' title='Col. 300GC &mdash; HL Deb 17 May 2004 vol 661 c300GC' name='column_300gc' href='#column_300gc' rel='bookmark'>300GC</a>
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-03884'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_495' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        15 (1) If&#x2014;
        <ol>
        <li>(a) the civil partners have been living apart for a continuous period exceeding 3 months, neither civil partner having deserted the other, and</li>
        <li>(b) one of the civil partners has been making periodical payments for the benefit of the other civil partner or of a child of the family,</li></ol>
        
        <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_301gc' title='Col. 301GC &mdash; HL Deb 17 May 2004 vol 661 c301GC' name='column_301gc' href='#column_301gc' rel='bookmark'>301GC</a>
        the other civil partner may apply to the court for an order under this Part.
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-03885'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_496' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        (2) An application made under sub-paragraph (1) must specify the total amount of the payments made by the respondent during the period of 3 months immediately preceding the date of the making of the application.
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-03886'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_497' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        (3) If on an application for an order under this Part the court is satisfied that the respondent has made the payments specified in the application, the court may make one or both of the orders set out in paragraph 16.
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-03887'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_498' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        (4) Sub-paragraph (3) is subject to the provisions of this Schedule.
      </p>
      <ol class='xoxo'>
        
      </ol>
      
